<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Michael Clarke has spoken out on his relationship with ex wife Kyly Clarke after the couple's split in February. </p>

<p>The former cricketer tells this week's Stellar that he has a 'great relationship' with his former wife of seven years. </p>

<p>The 39-year-old says that the focus for both he and Kyly is their daughter, Kelsey Lee, four, and the pair have come to an amicable custody arrangement without involving the courts. </p>

<p>New life: In an interview with this week's Stellar Magazine, Michael Clarke has spoken out on his relationship with ex wife Kyly Clarke after the couple's split in February. Pictured with the former couple's daughter Kelsey Lee </p>

<p>'I can sit here and say my daughter is the most important thing in my world. I've got a wonderful relationship and friendship with Kyly,' he told the magazine. </p>

<p>Michael explained that the former couple share custody fifty-fifty, each spending three days a piece with the toddler. </p>

<p>'At the moment we do three nights on, three nights off – that's our routine. Kyly and I talk daily to work out if that is best for Kelsey Lee,' he added. </p>

<p> Still close: The former cricketer says he has a 'great relationship' with his former wife of seven years. The 39-year-old says that the focus for both he and Kyly is their daughter, Kelsey Lee, four, and the pair have come to an amicable custody arrangement. All pictured </p>

<p> Close: 'I can sit here and say my daughter is the most important thing in my world. I've got a wonderful relationship and friendship with Kyly,' he told the magazine</p>

<p> Pals: Michael explained that the former couple share custody fifty-fifty, each spending three days a piece with the toddler. 'At the moment we do three nights on, three nights off – that's our routine. Kyly and I talk daily to work out if that is best for Kelsey Lee,' he added</p>

<p>Michael admits that being a single father has it's challenges, however. </p>

<p>'We always talk about single mothers; the challenges they face. But the single father faces challenges as well. </p>

<p>'There are things about Kelsey Lee that I learn every day. If I don't see her for three nights, I feel like my girl has turned six... As a parent, I'm absolutely no different to any other father,' he added.   </p>

<p>The interview comes after Kyly and Michael announced their $40million divorce after seven years of marriage. </p>

